issuetype.description: A problem which impairs or prevents the functions of the product.
issuetype.name: Bug

resolution.description: A fix for this issue is checked into the tree and tested.
resolution.name: Fixed

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.
status.name: Resolved

fields.description:
We should add support for a client token to be specified with euca-create-nat-gateway so that callers can ensure idempotency.

http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/APIReference/API_CreateNatGateway.html
http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/APIReference/Run_Instance_Idempotency.html

comments.body: This command will be new in the next series, so it does not require a release note.

*Eucalyptus Version*

{{4.3.1-0.25167.82.20161207git13777bb.el7}}

*Euca2ools Version*

{{3.3.1-0.1820.50.20161115gitdc4f158.el7}}

*Steps*

# Set up Eucalyptus 4.3.1 cloud with VPC - [hspencer-207|http://jenkins.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/job/Quick%20Launch%20Maint-4.3/207/]
# Created a subnet
{code}
[root@d-14 ~]# euca-create-subnet -c vpc-3c009bb0 -z evo 10.0.4.0/24 --region qa-admin@
SUBNET	subnet-06b70620	available	vpc-3c009bb0	10.0.4.0/24	251	evo	false	false
{code}
# Created a route table
{code}
[root@d-14 ~]# euca-create-route-table vpc-3c009bb0 --region qa-admin@
ROUTETABLE	rtb-9852b2c6	vpc-3c009bb0
ROUTE	local	active	10.0.0.0/16	CreateRouteTable
[root@d-14 ~]# euca-associate-route-table --subnet subnet-06b70620 rtb-9852b2c6 --region qa-admin@
ASSOCIATION	rtbassoc-193a3f96	rtb-9852b2c6	subnet-06b70620
{code}
# Allocated an EIP address
{code}
[root@d-14 ~]# euca-allocate-address -d vpc --region qa-admin@
ADDRESS	10.116.132.96	vpc	eipalloc-2d033fac
{code}
# Created an NAT Gateway
